af_omega_v2 (This is a bomb or de_ map.) Map Features: - 48 Spawns - Cubemaps - Radar Map - 2 Bomb Sites - Breakable Lights - Nav File w/ Place Names - 3D Skybox Map Information This map is an updated and optimized version of the original af_omega, which was also made solely by me. This map is everything that the original tried to be, and more. There have been a large number of changes since the original... The story behind the map is that some terrorists have decided to blow up LOL Mart's regional distribution center. The building is half warehouse, half offices. However, the police were tipped off and have secured the upper floor of the building. The terrorists arrived by the main road, killing the two officers stationed there. They have destroyed a section of the wall, and are ready to move in and blow up the building. Terrorists must bomb either the weapons cache in the warehouse, or the power transformers on the second floor to start an electrical fire, which will burn the building down. CT's must protect these areas and prevent the terrorists from detonating their weapon. Map Changes Optimization: I loaded the map with hint brushes, which let it have a big fps boost. There is no more lag on this map. However, players with low-end computers which normally get 30 fps or less may experience render lag for players walking around some corners. However, people with middle range (50+ fps) to good computers benefit from the changes. Looks & Functionality: As you can see, the map looks way better than the original. I re-did some of the surroundings, gave the map a new skybox, and made it feel more realistic. I also upgraded a lot of the lighting in certain places. The elevators now look better and run more like real ones, and the doors now look and behave better. You can now press E to open them, and the ones on the lower levels can have their glass panes shot out for added realism. The hole in the wall by T-Spawn has been widened, so it is now easier for players to jump through it. (2 at a time can fit) I also added an extra room in CT Spawn which let me get most of the CT spawn locations out of the big office area, so they don't get naded and awped by terrorists at the round start. The remaining ones are back against the far wall so they're safe. The ceiling was also raised in all of the office areas so it doesn't feel so cramped, and you don't hit the ceiling the second you hit jump. Breakable Lights: As with the original, this is two maps in one... A normal office building at night, and a shadowy haven of death when the lights get shot out. When the lights are gone, night vision is almost required... A flash light will help, but will get you spotted. You need to move around in teams to win here. Running in blindly will get you killed. I fixed some shading errors caused by the breakable lights, so now only one minor one appears out of the whole map. The lighting in the warehouse was also greatly improved, making it look more real. All of the custom textures along with the radar and .nav file are paked into the map, and should display properly in game. If you have problems, let me know. I appreciate any comments and assessments, and am more than happy to answer your questions. Thanks for playing!!

<font face="arial" color="#6666FF">af_omega
(This is a Defuse//Bomb or de map.)
Max Players: 48
Bomb Sites: 2

This, actually, is the first map I ever worked on.  It's been in progress for approximately 6 months...  It's not quite perfect (there are a few things I couldn't ever manage to get past involving lighting) but it is complete.

The map is a warehouse//office section of a department store called LOL Mart.  You can't access the department store areas...  It also has the street behind the building, and two other buildings near by.  The skybox gives the map an urban night setting.

Terrorists spawn at a police roadblock at a corner of the building.  After killing the two police officers there they have detonated a small bomb which destroyed a section of wall.  Terrorists can quickly infiltrate the building via the hole in the wall or run along the street to one of 5 doors.  (Three in the courtyard, one directly on the road, and another one right next to Bomb site A in the employee parking lot.)  Terrorists can also enter through an open loading door in the courtyard.  Ingenious players will use railings and cars in the courtyard to get to a window to break to gain access to the second floor.  There is a bomb site on the first floor in the warehouse area and one on the second floor near the elevators.

Counter Terrorists spawn on the second floor in between the two bomb sites.  They start off near the windows to the courtyard, so snipers can start shooting at each other almost as soon as the game starts.  Terrorists not wanting to get AWPed in the first few seconds can use the hole in the wall to rush the first floor which the CT's have a hard time accessing.  (Note that CT Spawn and T Spawn aren't in a line of sight with each other, it's just that if terrorists decide to go down the road not through the wall then they can either run and jump past the courtyard or throw nades or whatnot into the second floor windows that some of the CT's start about 12 feet away from...  Just play it to figure it out.)


Special Map Features:
- Cubemaps (Obviously)
- HUD Radar Map
- Destroyable Lights
- A Secret Knife Arena
- A Torture Chamber (For admins to use.)
- Two Working Elevators
- Humorous Motivational Posters (Custom)
- 1337UP Vending Machine Skin

About the Features:
Cubemaps:
Self Explanatory...  They're a little messed up upstairs though.  Look at the Destroyable Lights section as to why.

HUD Radar Map:
Just like the ones that all the default CS:S maps have.  Only problem is it can't show the first floor.  D:  Valve doesn't have many multi-level maps except like Assault, so they never worked out a 2-floor radar.  In any case, it rocks your socks.

Destroyable Lights:
The big fluorescent ceiling lights in the office areas and the hanging lights in the stairwells and the warehouse are breakable.  Shoot them and they turn off.  (Actually, shoot one and a group will go off, as though their circuit got fried.)  This makes af_omega two maps in one...  A normal-ish map and a map that requires teamwork and stealth to defeat the enemy.  It's an element that none of the classic maps have in them that I wanted to play with.  However, since Valve never had this in mind, when they made Hammer and Source SDK they weren't really meant for what I've done here.  This goes back to the map not being perfect.  In a couple of spots the shading on the walls, ceilings, or floors is messed up.  I've minimized the areas affected, but 4 remain.  They're rather minor though...  They just diminish the map's visual appeal some.  In any case, the breakable lights are fun to play with and definitely add to the map.

Secret Knife Area:
Admins can teleport players to the knife area.  It's on top of the office building right outside of T Spawn opposite the hole in the wall.

Torture Chamber:
Teleport problematic players in here for punishment.  It's behind the closed green door in CT Spawn next to the vending machines.

Two Working Elevators:
They work, but are exceptionally fast.  Not slow and lame like real ones lol.

Motivational Pictures:
Just look around the main building for these.  They're almost everywhere.

1337UP Vending Machine:
See the screen shots.  It should only work for this map.


Umm, yeah...

I hope y'all enjoy the map.
Questions and Comments are encouraged!!</font>

  I am thrilled to share this map with you. It's a real gem. Bots get around fine on this map; as you try it for the first time I recommend you start on the CT forces. Nintendo 64 N64 007 Goldeneye Temple map recreated for Counter Strike Source; it's fairly different; different enough to be an amazing Counter Strike Source map while retaining some 007 feel. map preview on youtube this has two bomb placement locations; technically four bomb locations if you count lower and upper levels as separate(actually there is 6 locations if you plant it hanging off the ledge of the upper level the bomb will float-no problem can still be defused). The fist bomb site  is close to T spawn, however go the distance to the further bomb site and there are far more hiding spots to  snipe a defuser so it's a nice trade off. Easily move between the upper and lower levels of the map; many choke points for conflict.  
Bots work nicely with this map; though the first few rounds they tend to travel in groups.  I hope this see this on regular rotation on many servers one day! 

I hope you find this map to be of great quality and share with others! I look forward to seeing many reviews of this map!

Urban Neighborhood 2 - Hostage Rescue
by Will2k


Overview
--------
This map is a source remake of my own map cs_urban2 for counterstrike 1.5 from back in 2002. 

This is my 2nd conversion from Goldsrc to Source (after cs_calm_source last week). I used some free time to convert this map while working on a full fledged bomb/defuse map for CS source.

I used existing resources from CSS / HL2. No new textures/materials, no new sounds, no new models. I also kept the layout of the original map without adding new areas; however, I added lots of details and a 3D skybox.

The map is small to medium size fitting up to 20 players.



Installation
------------
Simply extract the 4 files in the zip archive to your \Counter-Strike Source\cstrike\maps folder

I have included a nav file for offline play with bots.

Enjoy the map and have fun playing it as I had fun making it


Will2k

December 28, 2010
